column49: I have soooooooo many parents that aren't into the digital ordering. The kids, Scholastic, and I would be missing out so much if I didn't allow parents to submit orders to me in class like the old days. This new process has caused me hours of extra work now that tax is being added to items. I wish that was already factored into the cost of the book. Now I'm dealing with making change for families that aren't comfortable with placing orders online. It's such a shame because kids love getting those catalogs and browsing through them to choose books. It was so easy for families to check off the books they wanted and send it to me with their payment. I loved being able to sort the orders online by student name. Please, please, please, go back to offering in class ordering in addition to online.

column49: I am not enjoying Scholastic News as I did in the past.  I can tell there was a change with the order forms that go home, and I do not think the families are as interested in the books either.  Often I would send 2 or 3 order forms to my first grade families each month, including 2nd grade book order forms.  I only had one parent order in October and it did not equal $25 or more so I had to buy some books to avoid a charge for shipping.  It seems that there is less gifts for me to choose from.  I did not see book coupons that I can purchase to allow the kids to pick out a free book (from a coupon that I used to send home).  I used to get free books from my first book order too and save it as a Christmas gift.  I might not send the flyers home for my next years class if the interest seems to drop.
